frameDefinitions: This frame contains verbs and nouns that communicate the act of a Speaker to address a Message to some Addressee using language.

The Becoming_detached frame covers two situations: a scene in which one thing comes to be physically detached from something else; or a scene in which two things come to be disconnected from each other.
A Communicator or Medium briefly references something in a Message, in which only a subpart of the full content is profiled.
An object (the Theme) moves away from a Source.
A Speaker mentions a Specified_entity filling a Role, thereby providing information which supports a point of the Speaker.
A Communicator or Medium assigns linguistic meaning to an Unresolved_referent thereby identifying the specific actor or entity which fulfills the answer to this question.
frameExamples: I now <t>declare</t> you members of this Society.
The ship became <t>decoupled</t> from the dock.
The General Secretary <t>mentions</t> some of them in his report.
He cites the chief original observations <t>adduced</t> by Darwin as evidence for his theory.
Can you <t>name</t> all the U.S. Presidents?
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Speaker</fen> is the sentient entity that produces the <fen>Message</fen> (whether spoken or written).  It is normally expressed as the External Argument of predicative uses of the <t>target	</t> word, or as the Genitive modifier of the noun.
The <fen>Message</fen> is the role that identifies the content of what the <fen>Speaker</fen> is communicating to the <fen>Addressee</fen>.  It can be expressed as a clause or as a noun phrase.
The <fen>Topic</fen> is the subject matter to which the <fen>Message</fen> pertains. It is normally expressed as a PP Complement headed by 'about', but in some cases it can appear as a direct object.
<fen>Medium</fen> is the physical entity or channel used by the <fen>Speaker</fen> to transmit the statement.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the <fen>Message</fen> is made.
The role specifies the location where the <fen>Message</fen> takes place.
This role identifies the <fen>Item</fen> that detaches from the <fen>Source</fen>.
<fen>Source</fen> identifies the location to which an <fen>Item</fen> was attached before getting detached.

This role identifies the plural <fen>Items</fen> that are becoming detached from each other, resulting in their separation.


Notice that when the role <fen>Items</fen> occurs, neither <fen>Item</fen> nor <fen>Source</fen> can occur.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Item</fen> becomes detached from the <fen>Source</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Item</fen>  becomes detached.
The person who uses language in the written or spoken modality to convey a <fen>Message</fen> to another person.
A proposition or set of propositions that the <fen>Communicator</fen> wants the <fen>Addressee</fen> to believe or take for granted.
The physical or abstract setting in which the <fen>Message</fen> is conveyed.
The relevant entity or state-of-affairs that the <fen>Communicator</fen> mentions.
When the the <fen>Message</fen> is mentioned.
The location where the <fen>Communicator</fen> communicates the <fen>Message</fen>.
This is the object which moves. It may be an entity which moves under its own power, but it need not be.

All the verbs in this frame express some change of location, away from one place and to another. Any constituent that expresses the initial position of the <fen>Theme</fen>, before the change of location, is tagged with <fen>Source</fen>. Often the <fen>Source</fen> is understood from context.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the departure takes place.
The <fen>Place</fen> is the location in which the departing takes place.
The <fen>Speaker</fen> is the person who specifies the <fen>Role</fen> to be filled by the <fen>Specified_entity</fen>.
<fen>Medium</fen> is the physical entity or channel used by the <fen>Speaker</fen> to transmit the statement.
The entity that the <fen>Speaker</fen> identifies as filling a particular <fen>Role</fen>.
A slot in a particular or generic event or relation whose filler the <fen>Speaker</fen> identifies.
The time when the statement is made.
The role specifies the place where the statement takes place.
The person who uses language in the written or spoken modality to convey the <fen>Unresolved_referent</fen> to another person.
The thing to which the <fen>Communicator</fen> or <fen>Medium</fen> refers for identification purposes.
The physical or abstract setting in which the <fen>Unresolved_referent</fen> is conveyed.
When the the <fen>Communicator</fen> is makes the indication.
The location where the <fen>Communicator</fen> or <fen>Medium</fen> indicates the <fen>Unresolved_referent</fen>.

main reason for the decision to close down the New Orleans facility.

<fex>yesterday</fex> as the prime causes for the rising floodwaters
